# WHAT IT IS
#   Huber is a "package manager for GitHub-released binaries" —
#   point it at any GitHub project that publishes release
#   artifacts and Huber installs, version-locks, updates, and
#   uninstalls the binary inside an XDG-managed local prefix
#   (no privileged operations).  Concretely:
#     • `huber install <PACKAGE>` resolves the package via
#       Huber's curated YAML registry (`huber repo` manages
#       the list), downloads the matching release artifact
#       from GitHub's API, extracts it, and symlinks the
#       binary into `~/.huber/bin/` (which the user puts on
#       PATH)
#     • `huber update` walks every installed package and bumps
#       to the latest release tag
#     • `huber lock` / `huber unlock` pin versions so `update`
#       skips them
#     • `huber save` / `huber load` round-trip the installed-
#       package list as a YAML file for fleet-management
#       (think `Brewfile`-style provisioning)
#     • `huber search` / `huber show` / `huber info` /
#       `huber current` enumerate / inspect the registry +
#       installed state
#     • `huber repo` add / remove / list third-party Huber
#       registries (a registry is just a directory of YAML
#       package descriptors)
#     • `huber self-update` upgrades the Huber binary itself
#       via the same GitHub-Releases path
#     • `huber completions <shell>` emits shell completion
#       scripts for bash / zsh / fish / powershell / elvish
#       via `clap_complete`
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from huber/src/bin/huber.rs
#                       clap-derive `Cli` struct + huber/src/
#                       cmd/mod.rs `Commands` enum, with
#                       per-subcommand `*Args` structs in
#                       huber/src/cmd/*.rs; extracted via
#                       `gh api repos/innobead/huber/contents/
#                       huber/src/...`)
#
#   huber [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options  (every subcommand):
#     -l, --log-level <LEVEL>        Log level
#                                    (off | error | warn |
#                                     info | debug | trace)
#     --github-token <TOKEN>         GitHub token (optional
#                                    until reaching the rate
#                                    limit of GitHub API)
#                                    [env: GITHUB_TOKEN]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     install <PACKAGE>...           Install packages
#     uninstall <PACKAGE>...         Uninstall packages
#     update [<PACKAGE>...]          Update installed packages
#                                    to their latest released
#                                    versions
#     current <PACKAGE>...           Update the current package
#                                    versions
#     show                           Show installed packages
#     info <PACKAGE>                 Show package information
#     search <QUERY>                 Search package registry
#     lock <PACKAGE>...              Lock packages (or show
#                                    locked packages with no
#                                    args)
#     unlock <PACKAGE>...            Unlock packages
#     save <FILE>                    Save the installed-package
#                                    list to a YAML file
#     load <FILE>                    Load installed packages
